node.text:
The glacier on top of Mount Kebnekaise is Sweden’s last surviving mountaintop glacier.

And it’s shrinking. 

The mountain’s southern peak shrunk seven feet in just the past year. 

Scientist say warming temperatures and changing wind patterns are responsible for the rapid shrinking. 

Tap the link in our bio to learn more.

Photo: Lars Thulin/Getty Images

#ClimateChange #Sweden #MountKebnekaise #weather

Satellite images show us just how much Nevada's Lake Mead has dwindled in the past year. 

This week, the U.S. Bureau of Reclamation declared the first-ever water shortage on the Colorado River basin, including Lake Mead, the country’s largest reservoir.

The reservoir reached historically low water levels this summer, and is currently at 35% capacity.
